1
00:00:02,061 --> 00:00:05,709
<i>We are under assault. I
repeat, we are under assault.</i>

2
00:00:05,983 --> 00:00:08,748
<i>Aliens are dead, sliced open...</i>

3
00:00:09,850 --> 00:00:13,491
<i>Requesting aid from any
vessel within range...</i>

4
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:21,470
<i>Our crew is made of Asgardian
families, we have very few soldiers here.</i>

5
00:00:21,471 --> 00:00:25,472
<i>This is not a war craft, I
repeat, this is not a war craft.</i>

6
00:00:38,535 --> 00:00:41,753
Hear me... and rejoice.

7
00:00:45,339 --> 00:00:47,541
You have had the privilege

8
00:00:47,741 --> 00:00:50,620
of being saved
by the Great Titan.

9
00:00:53,313 --> 00:00:55,867
You may think this is suffering.

10
00:00:56,751 --> 00:00:58,272
No.

11
00:00:58,472 --> 00:01:01,025
It is salvation.

12
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:07,133
Universal scales

13
00:01:07,333 --> 00:01:10,920
tipped toward balance
because of your sacrifice.

14
00:01:12,335 --> 00:01:13,762
Smile

15
00:01:13,962 --> 00:01:16,606
for even in death

16
00:01:16,906 --> 00:01:19,843
you have become
Children of Thanos.

17
00:01:34,844 --> 00:01:37,749
I know what it's like to lose.

18
00:01:38,785 --> 00:01:42,701
To feel so desperately
that you're right,

19
00:01:42,901 --> 00:01:45,349
yet to fail nonetheless.

20
00:01:53,348 --> 00:01:55,476
As lightning

21
00:01:55,676 --> 00:01:58,694
turns the legs to jelly.

22
00:02:00,771 --> 00:02:03,825
I ask you
to what end?

23
00:02:04,380 --> 00:02:07,661
Dread it, run from it...

24
00:02:07,923 --> 00:02:10,485
Destiny arrives all the same.

25
00:02:11,548 --> 00:02:13,514
And now, it's here.

26
00:02:13,824 --> 00:02:15,790
Or should I say...

27
00:02:17,290 --> 00:02:18,821
I am.

28
00:02:23,959 --> 00:02:26,154
You talk too much.

29
00:02:26,779 --> 00:02:28,326
The Tesseract.

30
00:02:28,526 --> 00:02:31,013
Or, your brother's head.

31
00:02:35,426 --> 00:02:37,668
I assume you have a preference?

32
00:02:38,808 --> 00:02:40,433
Oh, I do.

33
00:02:42,855 --> 00:02:44,190
Kill away.

34
00:02:59,037 --> 00:03:00,685
All right, stop!

35
00:03:03,802 --> 00:03:08,012
We don't have the Tesseract.
It was destroyed on Asgard.

36
00:03:19,536 --> 00:03:22,192
You really are the worst, brother.

37
00:03:26,365 --> 00:03:30,724
I assure you, brother. The
sun will shine on us again.

38
00:03:32,239 --> 00:03:35,607
Your optimism is
misplaced, Asgardian.

39
00:03:35,661 --> 00:03:39,918
Well, for one thing,
I'm not Asgardian.

40
00:03:39,992 --> 00:03:41,430
And for another...

41
00:03:42,978 --> 00:03:44,962
we have a Hulk.

42
00:03:56,842 --> 00:03:58,740
Let him have his fun.

43
00:04:50,637 --> 00:04:52,387
Forefathers...

44
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:58,811
Let the dark magic, flow
through me one last... time.

45
00:05:13,956 --> 00:05:15,870
That was a mistake.

46
00:05:21,288 --> 00:05:22,561
No!

47
00:05:32,112 --> 00:05:35,150
You are going to die for that!

48
00:05:46,063 --> 00:05:48,469
My humble personage...

49
00:05:49,321 --> 00:05:53,110
bows before your grandeur.

50
00:05:54,782 --> 00:05:58,049
No other being, has
ever had the might,

51
00:05:58,423 --> 00:06:00,118
nay, the nobility,

52
00:06:00,763 --> 00:06:05,758
to wield not one,
but two Infinity Stones.

53
00:06:08,588 --> 00:06:10,350
The Universe,

54
00:06:10,550 --> 00:06:13,666
lies within your grasp.

55
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:56,020
There are two more
Stones on Earth.

56
00:06:56,543 --> 00:07:00,315
Find them, my Children, and
bring them to me on Titan.

57
00:07:00,347 --> 00:07:04,542
- Father, we will not fail you.
- If I might, interject...

58
00:07:04,574 --> 00:07:06,027
If you're going to Earth,

59
00:07:06,194 --> 00:07:08,652
you might want a guide.

60
00:07:08,653 --> 00:07:11,372
I do have a bit of
experience in that arena.

61
00:07:11,419 --> 00:07:13,856
If you consider failure experience.

62
00:07:14,056 --> 00:07:16,559
I consider experience, experience.

63
00:07:17,856 --> 00:07:19,527
Almighty Thanos.

64
00:07:19,806 --> 00:07:24,794
I, Loki, Prince of Asgard...

65
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:30,387
Odin-son...

66
00:07:33,262 --> 00:07:35,638
The rightful king of Jotunheim,

67
00:07:35,902 --> 00:07:38,426
God of Mischief...

68
00:07:38,473 --> 00:07:40,724
Do hereby pledge to you,

69
00:07:41,423 --> 00:07:45,284
my undying fidelity.

70
00:07:56,158 --> 00:07:58,064
"Undying"?

71
00:08:01,095 --> 00:08:04,431
You should choose your
words more carefully.

72
00:08:25,165 --> 00:08:26,329
You...

73
00:08:27,306 --> 00:08:30,024
will never be...

74
00:08:31,587 --> 00:08:33,149
a god.

75
00:08:58,933 --> 00:09:02,136
No resurrections this time.

76
00:09:24,874 --> 00:09:27,694
No... Loki...

77
00:10:06,102 --> 00:10:09,125
Seriously? You don't
have any money?

78
00:10:09,150 --> 00:10:12,454
Attachment to the material is
detachment from the spiritual.

79
00:10:12,479 --> 00:10:13,838
I'll tell the guys at the deli.

80
00:10:13,874 --> 00:10:16,439
Maybe they'll make you a
metaphysical Ham and Rye.

81
00:10:16,464 --> 00:10:18,976
- Wait, wait. I think I got a 200.
- Dollars?

82
00:10:19,001 --> 00:10:20,947
- Rupees.
- Which is?

83
00:10:24,426 --> 00:10:26,816
I wouldn't say no
to a Tuna Melt.

84
00:10:39,018 --> 00:10:40,768
Thanos is coming.

85
00:10:41,346 --> 00:10:42,947
We've got to...

86
00:10:47,038 --> 00:10:48,164
Who?

87
00:10:57,469 --> 00:10:59,172
Slow down. I'm
totally not kidding.

88
00:10:59,197 --> 00:11:00,462
- No, I'm not.
- Your rambling lost me.

89
00:11:00,486 --> 00:11:03,531
Look, you know how you're having a
dream, and in the dream you gotta pee?

90
00:11:03,556 --> 00:11:04,296
Yeah.

91
00:11:04,308 --> 00:11:06,563
Okay, then you're like, my
God, there's no bathroom,

92
00:11:06,588 --> 00:11:08,017
what am I gonna do? Oh!
Someone's watching!

93
00:11:08,041 --> 00:11:11,012
Right. And then you wake up, and in
real life you actually have to pee.

94
00:11:11,037 --> 00:11:12,377
- Yes.
- Yeah.

95
00:11:12,404 --> 00:11:13,461
Everybody has that.

96
00:11:13,473 --> 00:11:15,865
Right. That's the point
I'm trying to make.

97
00:11:15,881 --> 00:11:19,708
Last night, I dreamt,
we had a kid.

98
00:11:19,928 --> 00:11:21,327
So real.

99
00:11:21,527 --> 00:11:23,396
We named him after
your eccentric uncle.

100
00:11:23,428 --> 00:11:26,396
- What was his name? Porsey. Morgan.
- Right.

101
00:11:26,717 --> 00:11:30,304
So you woke up,
and we were...

102
00:11:30,329 --> 00:11:31,579
- Expecting.
- Yeah.

103
00:11:31,587 --> 00:11:32,494
- Yes?
- No.

104
00:11:32,519 --> 00:11:35,972
- I had a dream about it. It was so real.
- If you wanted to have a kid...

105
00:11:36,011 --> 00:11:38,040
You wouldn't have done that.

106
00:11:38,065 --> 00:11:39,270
I'm glad you brought this up

107
00:11:39,347 --> 00:11:41,979
cause it's nothing,
just a housing unit for nano-parts.

108
00:11:42,004 --> 00:11:44,702
- It's not helping your case. OK?
- It's an attachment. It's not a...

109
00:11:44,726 --> 00:11:47,311
- You don't need that.
- I know. I had the surgery.

110
00:11:47,335 --> 00:11:50,384
I'm just trying to protect us.
The future, as is, and that's it.

111
00:11:50,409 --> 00:11:53,096
Just in case there's a monster in
the closet. Just letting you know.

112
00:11:53,127 --> 00:11:54,714
Shirts.

113
00:11:55,846 --> 00:11:57,533
You know me so well.

114
00:11:57,932 --> 00:11:59,787
You finish all my sentences.

115
00:12:00,042 --> 00:12:02,908
You should have shirts
in your closet.

116
00:12:02,940 --> 00:12:05,707
Yeah. You know what
there should be?

117
00:12:05,732 --> 00:12:08,646
No more surprises. We'll
have a nice dinner tonight.

118
00:12:10,919 --> 00:12:13,928
We should have no more surprises.
Ever. I should promise you.

119
00:12:13,953 --> 00:12:15,609
- Yeah.
- I will.

120
00:12:18,312 --> 00:12:21,487
Tony Stark,
I'm Dr. Stephen Strange.

121
00:12:21,687 --> 00:12:24,069
I need you to come with me.

122
00:12:25,069 --> 00:12:27,834
Oh. Congratulations on
the wedding, by the way.

123
00:12:27,859 --> 00:12:29,917
I'm sorry. You giving
out tickets or something?

124
00:12:29,927 --> 00:12:31,243
We need your help.

125
00:12:31,827 --> 00:12:35,287
Look, it's not overselling it to say that
the fate of the Universe is at stake.

126
00:12:35,304 --> 00:12:37,842
And who's "we"?

127
00:12:38,428 --> 00:12:41,311
- Hey, Tony.
- Bruce!

128
00:12:45,436 --> 00:12:47,654
You okay?

129
00:12:48,747 --> 00:12:50,797
From the dawn of the Universe,

130
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:54,653
there was nothing.
Then, boom!

131
00:12:55,277 --> 00:12:58,723
The Big Bang sends
six elemental crystals,

132
00:12:58,923 --> 00:13:01,876
hurdling across the virgin Universe.

133
00:13:02,798 --> 00:13:04,272
These Infinity Stones

134
00:13:04,372 --> 00:13:07,265
each control an essential
aspect of existence.

135
00:13:08,267 --> 00:13:09,766
Space.

136
00:13:10,618 --> 00:13:12,305
Reality.

137
00:13:13,359 --> 00:13:14,929
Power.

138
00:13:15,539 --> 00:13:17,132
Soul.

139
00:13:18,016 --> 00:13:19,750
Mind.

140
00:13:21,149 --> 00:13:23,156
And Time.

141
00:13:32,076 --> 00:13:34,661
- Tell me his name again.
- Thanos.

142
00:13:34,701 --> 00:13:38,115
He's a plague, Tony. He invades planets.
He takes what he wants.

143
00:13:38,139 --> 00:13:42,021
He wipes out half the population.
He sent Loki.

144
00:13:42,779 --> 00:13:45,451
The attack on New York. That's him.

145
00:13:48,596 --> 00:13:50,455
- What's our time line?
- No telling.

146
00:13:50,463 --> 00:13:52,130
He has the Power and Space Stones,

147
00:13:52,230 --> 00:13:54,806
that only makes him the strongest
creature in the whole Universe.

148
00:13:54,831 --> 00:13:57,730
If he gets his hands, on
all six Stones, Tony...

149
00:13:57,755 --> 00:14:01,636
He can destroy life on a scale
of hitherto hundredth of.

150
00:14:01,661 --> 00:14:03,512
Did you seriously just say
"hitherto hundredth of"?

151
00:14:03,536 --> 00:14:05,869
Are you seriously leaning on
the Cauldron of the Cosmos?

152
00:14:05,969 --> 00:14:06,980
Is that what that is?

153
00:14:09,888 --> 00:14:11,927
I'm going to allow that.

154
00:14:13,985 --> 00:14:15,150
If Thanos needs all six,

155
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:17,283
why don't we just stick this
one down the garbage disposal?

156
00:14:17,383 --> 00:14:18,418
No can do.

157
00:14:18,430 --> 00:14:21,495
We swore an oath to protect
the Time Stone with our lives.

158
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:24,870
And I swore off dairy, but Ben &
Jerry's named a flavor after me, so...

159
00:14:24,879 --> 00:14:26,658
- Stark Raving Hazelnuts.
- It's not bad.

160
00:14:26,683 --> 00:14:27,934
A bit chalky.

161
00:14:28,134 --> 00:14:29,933
"A Hunka-Hulka Burning
Fudge" is our favorite.

162
00:14:29,941 --> 00:14:32,620
- That's a thing?
- Whatever. Point is, things change.

163
00:14:32,629 --> 00:14:35,301
Our oath to protect the
Time Stone cannot change.

164
00:14:35,309 --> 00:14:37,516
This Stone may be the best
chance we have against Thanos.

165
00:14:37,616 --> 00:14:40,575
And still conversely, it may also be
his best chance against us!

166
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:42,245
Only if we don't do our jobs.

167
00:14:42,270 --> 00:14:45,395
What is your job exactly,
besides making balloon animals?

168
00:14:45,751 --> 00:14:48,523
Protecting your
reality, douche bag.

169
00:14:48,548 --> 00:14:51,688
Okay guys, can we quick cable
this discussion right now?

170
00:14:51,713 --> 00:14:55,087
The fact is we have the stone.
We know where it is.

171
00:14:55,104 --> 00:14:57,572
Vision is out there somewhere
with the Mind Stone.

172
00:14:57,575 --> 00:14:59,604
And we have to find him now.

173
00:15:00,049 --> 00:15:02,697
- Yeah, that's the thing.
- What do you mean?

174
00:15:02,721 --> 00:15:06,158
Two weeks ago, Vision turned off
his transponder. He's offline.

175
00:15:06,167 --> 00:15:07,346
What?

176
00:15:07,519 --> 00:15:11,142
- Tony, you lost another super bot?
- I didn't lose him. He's more than that.

177
00:15:11,167 --> 00:15:14,065
- He's evolving.
- Who could find Vision, then?

178
00:15:18,289 --> 00:15:20,890
- Probably Steve Rogers.
- Oh, great.

179
00:15:20,914 --> 00:15:23,687
Maybe. But...

180
00:15:27,227 --> 00:15:28,852
Call him.

181
00:15:29,047 --> 00:15:30,812
It's not that easy.

182
00:15:31,352 --> 00:15:33,729
God, we haven't caught up in a spell,
have we?

183
00:15:34,436 --> 00:15:36,743
The Avengers broke up.
We're toast.

184
00:15:36,891 --> 00:15:38,484
Broke up?

185
00:15:39,836 --> 00:15:44,250
- Like a band? Like The Beatles?
- Cap and I fell out hard.

186
00:15:44,860 --> 00:15:47,078
We're not on speaking terms.

187
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:50,375
Tony, listen to me.

188
00:15:51,079 --> 00:15:53,406
Thor's gone.

189
00:15:54,141 --> 00:15:57,961
Thanos is coming. It doesn't matter
who you're talking to or not.

190
00:16:36,191 --> 00:16:39,675
Say, Doc, you wouldn't happen to
be moving your hair, would you?

191
00:16:39,768 --> 00:16:42,190
Not at the moment, no.

192
00:17:14,324 --> 00:17:15,784
You okay?

193
00:17:17,410 --> 00:17:20,277
- Help him. Wong, Doc.
- Got it.

194
00:17:20,302 --> 00:17:23,309
- Friday, what am I looking at?
- Not sure. I'm working on it.

195
00:17:23,334 --> 00:17:26,755
You better not put that Time
Stone in your back pocket, Doc!

196
00:17:26,780 --> 00:17:28,677
I might wanna use it.

197
00:17:55,178 --> 00:17:57,897
Ned, hey. I need you
to cause a distraction.

198
00:17:57,907 --> 00:17:59,217
Holy shit!

199
00:17:59,287 --> 00:18:03,747
We're all gonna die!
There's a spaceship!

200
00:18:12,098 --> 00:18:13,650
What's the matter with you kids?

201
00:18:13,689 --> 00:18:16,199
You never seen a spaceship before?

202
00:18:27,655 --> 00:18:31,701
Friday, evac anyone south of 43rd
Street, notify first responders.

203
00:18:31,717 --> 00:18:32,881
Will do.

204
00:19:00,935 --> 00:19:04,372
Hear me, and rejoice!

205
00:19:05,217 --> 00:19:09,529
You are about to die at the hands
of the Children of Thanos.

206
00:19:09,833 --> 00:19:14,450
Be thankful, that your meaningless
lives are now contributing to...

207
00:19:14,466 --> 00:19:17,497
I'm sorry, Earth is closed today.

208
00:19:17,513 --> 00:19:20,344
You better pack it up
and get outta here.

209
00:19:20,444 --> 00:19:21,856
Stone keeper...

210
00:19:22,247 --> 00:19:24,569
Does this chattering
animal speak for you?

211
00:19:24,594 --> 00:19:26,525
Certainly not. I speak for myself.

212
00:19:26,803 --> 00:19:30,054
There's no trespassing in
this city and on this planet.

213
00:19:30,242 --> 00:19:33,672
- You need to get lost, Squidward!
- They exhaust me.

214
00:19:33,742 --> 00:19:35,546
Bring me the Stone.

215
00:19:36,883 --> 00:19:38,937
Hey, do you want a piece?

216
00:19:39,679 --> 00:19:43,218
No, not really. But when
do I ever get what I want.

217
00:19:45,390 --> 00:19:48,936
Been a while. Good
to have you, buddy.

218
00:19:49,403 --> 00:19:52,787
I just... I need to
concentrate for a second.

219
00:19:52,812 --> 00:19:54,770
Come on, come on, Max.

220
00:19:57,439 --> 00:19:59,649
Where's your guy?

221
00:20:00,119 --> 00:20:01,892
I don't know. We're
certainly having a thing.

222
00:20:01,917 --> 00:20:05,542
There's no time for a thing. That's
the thing right there. Let's go.

223
00:20:11,622 --> 00:20:14,340
Dude, you're embarrassing me
in front of the wizards.

224
00:20:14,372 --> 00:20:16,840
- I can't... He won't...
- It's okay. Stand down.

225
00:20:16,865 --> 00:20:19,107
- Can I leave you with him? Thank you.
- I have him.

226
00:20:47,569 --> 00:20:52,169
- Where'd that come from?
- It's nano-tech. You like it? A little...

227
00:20:54,718 --> 00:20:58,511
Dr. Banner, if the rest of your
green friend won't be joining us...

228
00:21:07,759 --> 00:21:10,868
- You gotta get that stone outta here, now.
- It stays with me.

229
00:21:10,893 --> 00:21:12,525
Exactly. Bye!

230
00:21:21,496 --> 00:21:24,292
Tony, you okay? How we doing?
Good, bad?

231
00:21:24,317 --> 00:21:26,498
Really good. Do you plan on helping out?

232
00:21:26,598 --> 00:21:28,511
I'm trying. He won't come out.

233
00:21:38,167 --> 00:21:41,050
Come on, Hulk. What
are you doing?

234
00:21:41,120 --> 00:21:43,495
Come on. Come on! Come on!

235
00:21:43,526 --> 00:21:45,963
No!

236
00:21:49,526 --> 00:21:52,440
What do you mean, "no"?

237
00:21:57,175 --> 00:22:00,323
- Hey, man! What's up, Mr. Stark?
- Kid, where'd you come from?

238
00:22:00,347 --> 00:22:02,542
The field trip.

239
00:22:03,527 --> 00:22:06,232
What is this guy's problem, Mr.
Stark?

240
00:22:06,257 --> 00:22:09,858
He's from space, came here to
steal a necklace from a wizard.

241
00:22:36,008 --> 00:22:40,703
Your powers are quaint. You
must be popular with children.

242
00:22:42,531 --> 00:22:45,209
It's a simple spell
but quite unbreakable.

243
00:22:45,221 --> 00:22:47,432
Then I'll take it
off your corpse.

244
00:22:59,467 --> 00:23:05,248
You wouldn't. Removing a dead
man's spell... Troublesome.

245
00:23:05,264 --> 00:23:07,646
You'll only wish you were dead.

246
00:23:17,265 --> 00:23:18,687
No!

247
00:23:22,062 --> 00:23:24,655
- Kid, that's the wizard. Get on it.
- On it!

248
00:23:32,798 --> 00:23:35,157
Not cool.

249
00:23:49,291 --> 00:23:54,181
- Mr. Stark? I'm being beamed up.
- Hang on, kid.

250
